Sentencas: As a typical proton conductor, the perovskite structure BaZr0.1Ce0.7Y0.2O3-delta (BZCY) has a strong water absorption capacity, which occupies the reaction sites and reduces the oxygen partial pressure at the cathode side of proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells (H-SOFCs).
Titulo: A novel inhibiting water adsorption strategy to enhance the cathode electrocatalytic ability

Sentencas: To solve this problem, a strategy for water adsorption inhibition was proposed to prepare composite cathode using the cubic fluorite structure La2Ce2O7 (LCO).
Titulo: A novel inhibiting water adsorption strategy to enhance the cathode electrocatalytic ability

Sentencas: With much lower water absorption, when employing the mixed protonic and oxygen ionic conductor La1.85M0.15Ce2O7 (LMC, M=K, Rb, Cs) to replace the BZCY, the composite cathode LMC-La0.7Sr0.3FeO3-delta (LSF) possess higher open circuit voltage (OCV) and better electrochemical performance.
Titulo: A novel inhibiting water adsorption strategy to enhance the cathode electrocatalytic ability

Sentencas: In addition, the comparatively study of LMC-LSF series cathodes were also carried out to investigate the effect of large radius alkali metals substitution on the electrochemical properties.
Titulo: A novel inhibiting water adsorption strategy to enhance the cathode electrocatalytic ability

Sentencas: The cell with La1.85Rb0.15Ce2O7 (LRC)-LSF cathode reveals the most cell performance with the maximum power densities (MPDs) of 743, 547, 372, and 233 mW cm & minus;2 and the interfacial polarization resistance of 0.065, 0.148, 0.358, and 0.934 omega cm2 at 700-550 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: A novel inhibiting water adsorption strategy to enhance the cathode electrocatalytic ability

Sentencas: In general, LSF-LRC is a considerably potential cathode for H-SOFCs, and this strategy could inspire new ideas for designing and further optimizing new electrode materials.
Titulo: A novel inhibiting water adsorption strategy to enhance the cathode electrocatalytic ability
